Despite the hashtag hijacking, the NYPD is holding its head high.

NYPD spokesperson Deputy Chief Kim Y. Royster told the _[The New York
Times_](http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/23/nyregion/new-york-police-reach-out-
on-twitter-but-receive-a-slap-in-the-face.html?hpw&rref=nyregion&_r=1) that
the department was "creating new ways to communicate effectively with the
community" and that Twitter provided "an open forum for an uncensored
exchange" that is "good for our city."

