The NYPD's hashtag snafu is only the latest incident of its kind. This past
November, JPMorgan Chase introduced a #AskJPM hashtag for a live chat that
[quickly turned into a peg for harsh criticism and led the bank to cancel the
chat altogether](http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/229939). In perhaps a
more memorable incident, McDonald’s rolled out an #McDStories campaign in
early 2012 that was supposed to inspire customers to share positive stories
about their experiences at the fast-food chain, but instead inspired stories
about food poisoning and vomiting.

